  "body": "<!--\r\n  Note: if the issue is about documentation or the website, please file it at:\r\n  https://github.com/reactjs/reactjs.org/issues/new\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nAn enhancement\r\n\r\n**What is the current behavior?**\r\nhooks API is bundled in the react library\r\n\r\n**What is the expected behavior?**\r\nsplit hooks API into a seperate library\r\n\r\nReason:\r\n- 1.hooks is a API design, didn't have to be strictly related to/couple with specific library.\r\n- 2.I'm forced to translate a project written in react-hooks into vue.\r\nThanks to the hooks api and rxjs, 80% of my code don't need change, but I have to \r\n  - 2.1:hack in to replace the react hooks import syntax through webpack loader,\r\n  - 2.2:and use dummy file/declaration to hack the TS type check. \r\n  - If we have a react-hooks library, we can simply use NormalModuleReplacementPlugin to replace the import syntax from 「import {...} from \"react-hooks\"」 to「 import {...} from \"@myfork/vue-hooks\"」 and don't need to handle the TS type check in an ugly way.\r\n\r\n**Which versions of React, and which browser / OS are affected by this issue? Did this work in previous versions of React?**\r\n16.8.6\r\n",
